reviewText: The Hulk Hogan-Rick Flair strap match while a lame rerun of last year's show and looking more like a match that should have happened in the 80's instead in the 2000's it's still better then their bout in 1999. The WCW World heavyweight champioship match between Jeff Jarrett & Sid Vicious was a not great but still a pretty good solid match. The Terry Funk-Dustin Rhodes Bullrope match was good old-school solid brawl and could have done better without the giant chicken. The tag team match between the team fo Norman Smiley & The KISS Demon against the team of Lenny Lane & Rave was nothing then as The Nostalgia Critic would call it a "Big Lipped Alligator Moment" and the same goes for the 3 on 1 hanicap match for the WCW Hardcore title between Brain Knobbs & The Team of 3 Count(Evan Karagias,Shannon Moore & Shane Helms) eventhough it was a simi-good reminder of the 1990's ECW. The Vampiro-Fit Finlay Falls Count Anywhere match was pretty good. The Lumberjacks with Cast match bewteen Sting & Lex Luger was trash almost as bad as the movie:From Justin To Kelly. The rest were ok. I give this event a 6 out of 10.
Title: N/A
